reviews.text: Very nice theater. Quite charming. Good acoustics. Not too big or small. Perfect place to see a concert or play. I don't think there's a bad seat in the house.
Coolest venue in town. If you have an opportunity to see a show there DO it. I caught a Beatles tribute band and it was excellent. Not a bad seat in the house.

I was asked to go by a good friend and we had a delightful evening😄. I've enjoyed events at Peabody Auditorium for years, including the annual production of The Nutcracker Ballet. Last night was Johnny Mathis in concert. Although it's really not my taste in music, it was really good. Partly  because the Peabody is such a great small venue. I have physical limitations myself but thanks to the staff and ushers it was a really nice evening! And it's my understanding that most of the concert staff are volunteers. They were very helpful and seemed well organized😄

Anxiously awaiting Sound of Music on Thursday, March 21, 2019.  Driving from Orlando area with 16 others.  Having dinner at Peabody too.  All arranged so smoothly by Emilie, in charge of group sales.  Don't miss this amazing show that's been criss-crossing America for months now to rave reviews.

Nice overall experience.The building is fairly well kept, despite being 100 years old in 2018, the seats are comfortable and give good viewing angles. Interestingly, the bricks walls are exposed from inside giving it quite a unique look. Concessions were also well priced: $1 for snacks and $2 for drinks.
The Tortugas don't just care about baseball. They love the community. Thank you for supporting Aura of Hope Foundation and the bone marrow transplant patients we assist!

I worked for the Tortugas during the 2018 season and it was an experience I’ll never forget. Every home game was a blast with such high energy from the fans and the staff. Tickets are very affordable and they have different specials on food and drinks for different days of the week. Taco Tuesday? Yep! Thirsty Thursday? Double yep!! There were even all you can eat nights. The mascots, Sheldon and Shelly, steal the show and thrill the kids. If you live nearby or are visiting during baseball season you’ve got to go to a game and see what the hype is all about. I can’t wait for the 2019 season.
Great ballpark, prices, and atmosphere! Highly recommend if you are in Daytona Beach!

A great minor league and historical baseball park. Tickets are reasonably priced so you can take the whole family... as long as you don't eat.  Actually compared to some parks, their food prices aren't that bad.  Food is nothing special compared to the inventiveness of some parks, but it's ok. If you're a senior citizen, join the Silver Sluggers for about $30 and get a free t-shirt and free parking and admission to 12 games. Great deal. Also includes free soda or cup of coffee each of those games and beer specials.
Great time, everyone should go at east once.

Went for the spring Turkey Run aways a great time... Just not as much stuff this year. Saw so many cars. Definitely plenty to see plenty to eat. We only went for one day. Love the show. We didn't make a big purchase this time but always look for the deal of the day!!! See you in November!!

The Daytona International Speedway is amazing! The bleachers are kept clean, as well as the bathrooms. No worries about having to wait in line for the restrooms as there’s plenty around, equipped with a ton of stalls - did I mention how clean they are?! The staff during events are always kind, and are more than happy to point you in the right direction if you ask. There’s different restaurants on the inside like a BBQ spot, the Budweiser lounge and even a stop for tacos! I’m sure there’s much more - the place is HUGE! If you’re going to Daytona, this should be a destination for you - race fan or not!

A great track and amazing experience!  Traffic in and out can be challenging but with over 100,000 people attending the event you can't expect no delays.  Stadium seats are comfortable and the concessions are plentiful and varied for different tastes.  The entertainment is great and the event is one everyone should experience once in their lifetime!

I went to the event! Turkey Run, a car show of all types..$10. and no parking fee! Plenty of food had Hot dogs that the Boy Scouts had Delicious! Prior to the car they had a Flea Market..of Car items..had a great time . Affordable..in November , coming another car show.. double this event! Looking forward to Go!

The wife and I had a great time.  Huge swap meet. Bought items I had been looking for and things I had not planned, luckily I brought a cart.  Filled it. The amount of cars for sale was huge.  So many beauty cars.  Never made it to the show cars. After walking around 6 hours in the sun we were spent.  Had a great time, Highly Recommend for any car enthusiasts out there who hasn't gone.  There's a show in march and the big show in November.

Went for the spring Turkey Run aways a great time... Just not as much stuff this year. Saw so many cars. Definitely plenty to see plenty to eat. We only went for one day. Love the show. We didn't make a big purchase this time but always look for the deal of the day!!! See you in November!!

There's a show in march and the big show in November.
Love bringing my daughter to this park.  Always clean and def pet friendly
They redone the park again. It looks great. Always clean.Nice place to park your car and relax in the afternoon. Enjoy the view......
Park is great and loved the river breeze. Weird squirrel man was there feeding the squirrels a combination of flax seed and nuts and very enthusiastically video taping them. Seemed harmless though.
It's really nice. On the water. Has a shaded kids park.
Super chill place to hang out. Tennis courts have new lights. They are sweet.

I love this place!! Came here the other day after work and had to make it quick so I put $40 on high card and walked out with $140 in 15 minutes of walking through the doors. Quickest money I've ever made! Place is clean, has food and drinks! Definitely recommend!

First time to Daytona and visited the poker room with a good friend. He played cash while I played 1:00pm Wednesday tournament. Can't complain as 4 of us chopped at the end. Went back for the Sunday night tourney and ended up chopping that as well!  Dealers were very efficient and accurate. Very well run tourney. Can't wait to come back!!

The Astronaut is amazing to see when you walk in, the dog track is something I have never seen before- this was my 1st time watching Greyhounds race, they really are beautiful majestic animals, watching them run was a really interesting experience, I am a dog lover and have cared for animals for about 18 years. I played poker as well, the managers and floor people and cashiers were all real cool, I enjoyed my sessions here and really enjoyed how professional everything was. I will definitely be back and appreciate all the love I received on my visits here. 
Great place !! 5 stars

Came in around noon today. The poker room was already rather busy. The simulcast had a few people going back and forth but overall not too busy. The server at the "snack bar" and the two ladies at the front door were very nice and actually made me feel welcome to be there. I'm interested to see how much busier it would get later into the Friday night.

I went alone, would probably have had more fun of I had gone with a friend.  Dogs seemed like they were having a good time.  Tails were wagging and all had an alert demeanor. 

Go EARLY before the races if you want a table for lunch.  After the races begin people wont get up so that new diners can sit down for lunch. 

Very busy on the Wednesday matinee, pretty much standing room only when a rain shower came through. Mostly retired people at the Wednesday matinee.  Some children, but not too many that I couldn't get away from the misbehaved ones.  Long lines for making bets.  Staff was nice and friendly enough. 

I had enough fun that I will try again sometime with a companion.

Lived in Daytona most of my life. This has always been my go to place. Servers, bartenders are extremely friendly. Also very knowledgeable of there menus. It's a great place to take kids during the day. Come evening time it's more for adults to hang out and have a great time. Food is excellent. If your on a special diet they accommodate.

It is a really cool place filled with tons if memorabilia. I have not eat here. I usually just go for drinks. The drink prices are really good. The music is loud, but it is a fun atmosphere filled with happy people.

Ordered from Uber eats. The chicken wings were delicious! I couldn't get enough of that BBQ sauce, I'd be happy if my life were covered in that. The wings were also nice and crispy on the outside. Mac n cheese is regular but good!

One if the most amazing places I visited for bike week. I was here the last Saturday night of bike week the good drinks and nicest and most beautiful ladies. Made the whole trip worth going a MUST SEE..

Good place. Decent food. Drinks great although their shot prices are high. They have a nice selection of draft beers both imported, craft beers and domestic selections. Best thing on the menus are the burgers!  Big...juicy and very tasty. Right on the corner of Atlantic (A1A) and Main Street. Enjoy your burgers sitting in replica 'car' booths.

we stayed in Daytona for a cheer competition at the ocean center & loved this great find of a cafe! The staff was extremely friendly, patient and helpful.  We loved it so much we went twice in 2 days.  Chili was so good, had a breakfast wrap that even my picky eater kids loved and enjoyed a few delicious smoothies.  Highly recommend!

This is one of the best places I’ve ever been to. Smoothies are delicious and not expensive at all. Me and my boyfriend come there couple days a week. Everything is amazing, and everyone should really try California Chicken Club wrap and greens to the max smoothie, those are our favs.

So unbelievably slow. I needed one smoothie, and it took almost an hour to get my ONE smoothie. If you’re in a hurry I do not recommend this place, but if you have all damn day to wait for one smoothie this is your place

Phenomenal smoothies and healthy food in Daytona!!  I tried the mango bango and it was just what I needed... Super fresh ingredients and flavorful!  Lots of organic options.  Also tried a breakfast wrap and my wife had a green smoothie!  We loved it. Everything clean and fresh.  Great service!  Can't wait to go back and try more!  This place is a gem!

This place is beautiful from the inside out. From the moment you walk in until the moment you leave, you are greeted with enthusiasm and care. The food is delicious- all organic, all healthy and made from the heart. You can taste the quality. Daytona needed a place like this.

Had the hot pastrami sub. Plenty to eat and the pastrami was delicious. Very good quality pastrami and the swiss cheese was also. So happy to find this great shop! Cant find this sandwich anywhere and it was definitely worth it!. Friendly quick delivery as well. We will be back soon for more!
Huge sandwiches! Definitely get your money's worth here. Owner and staff are great to do business with.
The sub I got was delicious.  The guy who served me was awesome. Super chill. Five stars all around.
Decent quality. Ordered a Philly. Bread to meat ratio was not the best. Roll was good but could have used a bit more meat in it.
Great little establishment terrific food all at a great price
The food was excellent.   Very fresh and flavorful.   Accommodating staff.  All good!
Pho is good! The real star here is the banh mi; probably one of the best ones I’ve ever had!

Stopped in to get some Pho to take home, this place is charming.  The folks here are warm, welcoming and very helpful. The menu is very nice with some  very good looking Vietnamese offerings. The Pho was delicious, exceptionally fragrant and tasty.  This is definitely on my list of places to come back to.
This place is great if you have never been to a Vietnamese restaurant before. Otherwise it's pretty average quality food at prices where I'd expect better. Hit or miss on the service.

They have a full menu, but just soup, but the soup is excellent. A huge bowl of delectable broth, thin sliced beef, noodles (egg or rice), sprouts, fresh greens (mint, cilantro, basil and others) fresh jalapeño slices, and fresh lime.

This place was GREAT!! We are in town for a beach get away and wanted ice cream/fro-to with toppings and this was the closest to us. Made the drive from ocean front and was so worth it. We walked in to be greater by the young lady who helped us try flavors and her favorites. My daughter dropped her fro-yo right on the floor. I apologized and told her I would clean it, she was adamant that she would clean it up and not to worry about it, all with a genuine smile on her face (I scooped up what I could with napkins anyways). We enjoyed our treat and a young man came to mop up the mess. I apologized and made my girl do the same, he told her no worries accidents happen. So sweet! The vibe in here was very retro and cool. So were the uniforms, so much so we asked for a picture 😂 and he happily obliged. This was a great trip, very welcoming and sincere.

Great place to sit and eat several different flavors of frozen yogurt and sorbet. You can also bring your dog there's a bowl of dog biscuits for your pet as you walk in. Owners are proactive in the community. They are one of our small local businesses that I try to support. Come support your small local business!!!

New owner,this place use to to amazing and they were about helping rescue dogs but now its run down looking and their trying to do a 1950 decor but it's not good,there's only 4 flavors and now they put the topping on for you.looks like it's in the middle of a remodel or about to be closed.its sad

Their fro-yo and toppings are delicious, but I’m rating with two stars because twice in the past week I’ve driven from Ormond to come here and they’ve been closed(mind you the website says open). Sunday night was closed and tonight (Friday) was closed. 
Not cool... need to update your hours!!

Went in last night and met the new owner
They have lots planned to change this place into what daytona has been missing. I would recommend going there where you will find great service, yummy ice cream and a great atmosphere 
Thanks again!

I've gone on the tour two times now, and I enjoyed it just as much as the first time I went on the tour. I personally like the chocolate covered potato chips the most so it's nice that most of the time (if not all of the time) they are on a buy 2 get 1 free shelf. The tours are free for anyone wondering and you get two little treats to sample. Then you can go buy a bag of whatever you like in the store.

Super great chocolate at a pretty good price. I always love the way their chocolates look. They're presented so nicely but by far the most tasty chocolates. Anything from chocolate covered chips to bacon. Everything there is delicious and it's always hard to choose what you want. On top of it all, they always have a great deal going on. So I will be coming back for more soon!

Wonderful display of all types of chocolate, candies, fudge just about anything you can imagine. Also you can tour the candy making during certain hours. Its a delicious place to treat yourself and get gifts of sweets for special people.  Explore, shop and support genuine candy establishments rather than the same old mass produced candy..

Great little local homemade chocolate shop. The tour is a nice short look at the company's history and how they make their goodies. The free samples are definitely a bonus. Delicious chocolate and sweets. Chocolate covered bacon, the fudge, and their chocolate covered strawberries are all amazing.

Each time we visit Daytona we visit the factory. This time was no exception. All of their chocolate is hand made and it is by far the best chocolate we have ever tasted. They give tours and offer free samples at the end of the tour. They have light, dark, white, milk and every flavour imaginable. The staff are friendly, there is a washroom and there is parking in front and out back. A great place to visit when in Daytona.

I took my husband here for his birthday in April 2016 and everything was great. Our steaks were cooked absolutely perfect melt in your mouth. The drinks are less expensive than chain restaurants too. The only thing I can say that was not up to par was the relish plate they bring to you to start. It only had pickle chips on the plate. And the fresh bread was a tad browned too much on the bottom. But still tasty. The atmosphere my not be of this century, but it's supposed to be that way. The negative reviews as well as this positive one are of course just opinions of our dining experience. Give it a try and decide for yourself. ☺

This steakhouse has changed very little since my first visit 35 years ago.  Visiting there is like a journey in a time machine.  The dining area is neat and clean but aging.  The charm of this place is the attitude, the attentive service and especially the perfectly prepared steaks.  The shish kabob is a delicious favorite of mine.  The preparation of meat is an art for this old establishment.  Don't come here if you are in a hurry.  The pace slows at the entrance.  It's a celebration.  A great place for an anniversary or after a big sale.

Excellent. Although if you're not looking for it you'll drive right by the plain building. But the service and food will blow you away. By far the best meal I've ever eaten. It is family owned and operated since 1948 and they know exactly what they're doing! You won't be disappointed.

What an awesome steak house.  This is off the beaten beach path but it is so worth it.  The steaks are huge and cooked perfect.  Everything there has this old original the way a dining experience should be but you never get to take part in any more.  Thank you for a great dinner and reminding us all what going to dinner should be about.

I am deeply impressed by the staff of this restaurant.  We were there as part of a large group and there was an error with my meal.  Once again, we were part of a very large party and, as we all know, accidents can happen.  Each member of the staff apologized personally.  It is refreshing to see not just customer service, but accountability.  You got a strong sense that they were proud of where they worked and really wanted to reflect that.  We will patronize them next time by choice, not simply because we are part of an engagement held there.
I love this restaurant. Every time I go the food is mind blowing. It has a pretty neat atmosphere with Indian music playing lightly in the background. The service is wonderful as well.
Very good Indian cusine. Spiced to taste. Very enjoyable. Well worth it!! Server is also smoking hot!!
The food was delicious!!! & the service was great,  the owner was wonderful.  Cant wait to visit again!

Randomly went there yesterday evening as we were craving Indian food and wanted to try a new place. Really surprised with how good their food was. Scrumptious cuisine and excellent service. Ambience needs some work as it is a bit outdated but we left with a full bellies. Will absolutely eat there again.
Great food great people. If you have never had Indian food treat yourself to the best butter chicken in the world.

Good food, nice relaxed enviroment.  If you are looking for a quick bite, this is not the place.  That being said; the courses were spaced appropriately and my family enjoyed a good meal together without being rushed.  We will visit again when we are in the area.

TRULY A HIDDEN TREASURE!
A MUST PLACE TO DINE.
Please PLEASE try it You Will Not Regret it  
The AMBIANCE,  THE SERVICE AND FOOD IS DEFINITELY ONE TRILLION  + STARS .
You Will Not Be Disappointed. 
We went this evening and  AGAIN  I was NOT DISAPPOINTING
The wait staff was awesome very friendly. The food was amazing. I will definitely go back again.
Italian food and the setting at this place is excellent. Food was so delish. I will probably become a regular. The bill was reasonable I would say.
Excellent wine selection,  lovely bread, attentive wait staff.  No one rushed us out the door. I would recommend making reservations if dining later than 6p.

We went for my wife's birthday. Everything went as planned. I had called in advance for reservations and we got a table overlooking the water. It was a beautiful view. Our server named  Christopher was excellent. The food was great. I would definitely return for the next special occasion.
Don't listen to any of the bad reviews.  This place is amazing. We always make a point of coming here when we are in town. Great food and amazing service.  Make it a stop!

My wife and I easily made an online reservation and was greeted right at the door. The service was impeccable and very knowledgeable about the menu. The wine selection was grand and the food (and its presentation) was worth the money! Highly recommended for a night evening out with a loved on.

We came here for our 12-year anniversary... we did not have reservations and were told that there was open seating downstairs. We waited 20 minutes all of the tables were dirty we finally sat down at a dirty table and it took two different people three separate trips to clean the table off and get a drink and appetizer ordered. At the time of ordering the appetizer and drinks I also asked for some menus. Never got it. After we got our drinks and appetizer we enjoyed them. Our "waitress" finally came to check on us (everything was gone and drinks empty) we asked for a water and menus... Finally got a menu still no water... We were there over an hour finally we left $30 on the table and walked out. The door guy asked us how our experience was and all he could say was sorry. Didn't even try. We were sorry too.

This Chart House is something of a local institution in Daytona for a big night out. Next to a marina, with pleasant views and kind of an out of the way location - right in the middle of things, if that makes any sense. I can only speak to our experience, with a group of about 10 people out for a business dinner. I usually dread these kinds of evenings, because they can drag on forever, especially when the place is busy like it was for our time there. But I must say the staff absolutely blew away with their promptness and good service. We were in and out within two hours! New record! And we didn't feel rushed or anything. The food was very good (appetizers, salad, soup, main course, dessert) and the wines superb.

It is refreshing to see not just customer service, but accountability.  You got a strong sense that they were proud of where they worked and really wanted to reflect that.  We will patronize them next time by choice, not simply because we are part of an engagement held there.
Great food. Amazing dinner of spaghetti and bread. My family and I enjoyed our evening here and had a great time.

First time,  but a customer for a lifetime.  Amazing food that must be savored and enjoyed with the time and care it took to prepare. Made a reservation and was greeted by name upon entering...wonderful touch. Don't miss an opportunity to enjoy the wonderful food and service.
We had a party of 10.  All food came out HOT and fresh, and everyone LOVED their meal.  So so excellent!  Fantastic service as well.  GO!
The food here was excellent and came out very quickly after we ordered. The staff was also extremely nice

I went there two days in a roll. Very good place and gentle people, the service was one of the best that I’ve ever had. The food was amazing, the carpaccio was my favorite dish, they also serve a delicious bread as entry that was made at the pizza oven. The parking is free and the restaurant was very easy to find. The prices were good, around 20/30 dollars and the food very sofisticaste.

So glad to have found this place! Everything about it was fantastic. From the unique burger menu (which the glazed donut burger phenomenal), to the service. Just about any time any of the staff walked by they made sure we were doing good. All the food was top notch.

A note to all who want to experience something new... I read some not so positive comment, so I decided to visit the place and have a quick bite, and a beer 😁 just to figure out for myself to whether it was an isolated experience, or there is strong evidence to those comments. 

My observation; all though it's not the same as it was in my first experience, nevertheless it was enjoyable. Therefore I would have to still say " I recommend this place", and I do believe that maybe it was an isolated experience. 

I would definitely encourage their management to read all the post that regard to this business, and show acknowledgement and awareness, and maybe a response to show appreciation for the comment.. a simple thank you as a response goes a long way...

My husband and I ate here for the first time and had a great experience. Our waiter was very nice and attentive. I think his name was James, at least that's what the receipt said lol. I'm bad with names. My husband had the Drunken Monk, which he loved, and I had the Western. We both halved our burgers so we could each try one. I loved both, but my husband wasn't a fan of the Western. To each their own. We both got our burgers cooked to medium and they were very juicy! We also had the pretzel buns and they were delicious.  Definitely coming back to try out their other burgers. And definitely getting the beer battered onion rings again.

Not a bad place for a burger. Waited to be seated and did not get any attention (place was not busy). Decided to skip to the bar outside to eat. Service was a little quicker. I got the drunken monk burger and my other half got the morning teak. Burgers where cooked well and had great taste. However the sweet potato tots where under cooked and lacked some form of seasoning (brown sugar & cinnamon or even some sea salt would of been nice). My Onion rings were okay. Seem like they had been sitting a while. This place is like in an apartment area. So don't let the directions throw you off. The burgers were worth the money. They also have a burger challenge there. Maybe I will go for the challenge next time! 😏

At first the energy wasn’t friendly to me & I kind of feel that way still about the bartender (she didn’t seem happy at all). My waiter though, not only was he nice but he was very helpful when it came to choosing what to eat. The food was GREAT & the drinks. Nice atmosphere to hang out so I would definitely recommend this place. Prices aren’t inexpensive but not too much neither.
